== Overview ==
The '''{{tl|Ifexist check redirect}}''' and '''{{tl|Ifexist check redirect/if}}''' templates can be used to identify the status of an article: whether the article exists or not; if it does, whether it is blank, and/or whether an article is a redirect and what type of redirect it is (to a section of an article, or to the general article). This extends upon the use of {<nowiki />{[[mw:Help:Extension:ParserFunctions##ifexist|#ifexist]]}}, which will only check whether the page exists.

==Usage==
{{tl|Ifexist check redirect}} returns one of five values to determine the type of an article; these values are listed in first section of the table below.
: <code>{{tlx|Ifexist check redirect|ARTICLE}}</code>

{{tl|Ifexist check redirect/if}} provides the same function as {<nowiki />{[[mw:Help:Extension:ParserFunctions##if|#if]]}} and  {<nowiki />{[[mw:Help:Extension:ParserFunctions##ifexist|#ifexist]]}}, using the return value of the previous template to provide two cases if the article type matches what is required.
: <code>{{tlx|Ifexist check redirect/if|ARTICLE|ARTICLE TYPE|IF TRUE|IF FALSE}}</code>

